Crime Fiction - Recent Reads I love good crime fiction, and I&rsquo;ve been feasting on a variety of it in recent weeks. Here&rsquo;s a brief roundup&hellip;
Read on Substack&hellip;
Read on Medium&hellip;

Books: &ldquo;On the Grid: Life Behind the Scenes of Formula 1&rdquo; I just finished reading On the Grid: Life Behind the Scenes of Formula 1 by Luke Smith.
I&rsquo;ve been enjoying Luke Smith&rsquo;s coverage of F1 racing on The Athletic for a few years now, and so I was pleased to see that he has recently published a behind-the-scenes book.
Smith takes us behind the scenes at a variety of race locations, from Melbourne, Australia—where Luke has found the world’s greatest croissants—to the Circuit of the Americas in Austin, Texas to Belgium&rsquo;s infamous Spa circuit&hellip;

Books: &ldquo;Leave the Gun, Take the Cannoli&rdquo; I recently finished reading Leave the Gun, Take the Cannoli: The Epic Story of the Making of The Godfather by Mark Seal.
It&rsquo;s an entertaining read that runs from author Mario Puzo&rsquo;s writing of The Godfather through the casting, filming, and release of the Oscar-winning film. Seal delves into all aspects of the efforts to bring the novel to the screen&hellip;
