The Slow Horses of Slough House Many espionage stories&rsquo; protagonists fall into one of two categories&hellip;
The first category is the espionage professional: Ian Fleming&rsquo;s James Bond, Daniel Silva&rsquo;s Gabriel Allon, and John LeCarre&rsquo;s George Smiley all come to mind. Cool, calm, collected, they are trained and paid to do their nation&rsquo;s dirty work.
At the other end of the spectrum is the unwitting amateur that finds themselves thrust into a situation which they are seemingly ill-equipped to deal with.

Books: &lsquo;How We Got to Now: Six Innovations That Made the Modern World&rsquo; by Steven Johnson I just finished reading How We Got to Now: Six Innovations That Made the Modern World by Steven Johnson, and I enjoyed it quite a bit.
Goodreads rates it at 4.11 and I would say that is about right, if you enjoy history and science.
